Superman v2 #186-187
Publisher:  DC Comics
Publication Date:  September 4, 2002 and October 2, 2002

Writer:  Geoff Johns
Penciller:  Pasqual Ferry
Inker:  Cam Smith (#186) and Mark Farmer (#187)
Colorist:  Richard Horie and Tanya Horie
Letterer:  Richard Starkings
Cover:  Pasqual Ferry and Cam Smith (#186) and Pasqual Ferry and Dexter Vines (#187)

Superman v2 #186
"Ending Battle" part 1! When a revamped Master Jailer and Neutron attack the Capitol aiming for Pete Ross and Lana Lang, Superman must save his friends while uncovering clues to the mysterious mastermind behind it all. Continued in The Adventures of Superman #608.

Superman v2 #187
"Ending Battle" part 5, continued from Action Comics v1 #795. Superman returns to a Metropolis turned into a prison by the new Master Jailer. But that's not all! Guarding the gates of that prison are deadlier versions of the Prankster, Bizarro, Metallo, and a new female Puzzler. Continued in The Adventures of Superman #609.

Thanks goes to DreamGirl for this release.
